OverHistory.UPDCommentry: WICKET! Jess Kerr bowling to Shafali Verma, good length ball, pitching outside off stump, Shafali Verma a touch late on the flick, misses the ball as it sneaks past the inside edge and strikes her back pad. The bowler goes up in a loud appeal for LBW, and the umpire raises the finger. Shafali opts for the review, but the replays show no issues with the front foot, and UltraEdge confirms there's no bat involved. Ball-tracking shows three reds, impact in line, hitting the stumps, and the on-field decision stands. Shafali has to make the long walk back, and India loses a review early in the innings. WICKET Shafali Verma lbw Jess Kerr (India (Women) 19 Runs for 2 wickets)
